Using only the `by_val` line compiles fine:

``` rust
trait Foo {
    fn by_val(self) {}
    fn by_ref(&self) {}
}
impl Foo for int {}

fn main() {
    macro_rules! t (
        ($a:expr) => { {
            // $a.by_val(); $a.by_val();
            $a.by_ref(); $a.by_ref();
        } }
    );

    t!(1i);
}
```

